reviews.review_text:
Hot time on the old town tonight. One thing about getting these recordings up here is that I listen to shows I haven't listened to in a very long time. I'm listening to the second set this evening and remembering that we were set up right behind Adan Healy behind the board. There may have been 2 or 3 patches out of me and the day time heat was into the 100's. Due to this Dan had a tarp over the top of the sound board area, which of course obstructed the view and the sound. By the time the Dead came out for the second set the sun was setting and the temperature had dropped. I asked Dan if he would be kind enough to drop the top. He agreed and the crew took down the tarp, opening up our view as well as sound. 

All in all, for 1993 shows, these aren't too bad, as things went steadily down hill from here. Further, after Dan left, the sound went way south with the terrible mono mix that was sent by Cutler. Cutler's mix was a big step back in PA sound, IMO. Listen to the separation that Dan has here with his stereo mix, then listen a mono mix from John. I think I know which you will prefer. If sound were chocolate ice cream Dan's would taste like rich and creamy premium chocolate. John's would taste like brown.
